}\pard\qj\sl240\slmult1 \sb120 \fi0 {\s4\ql\sb240\sa60\keepn\f13\b\fs32 {\*\bkmkstart BMex_pred_v}2.3{\*\bkmkend BMex_pred_v}  No limitations on which semantic units can be chosen as predicates\par
}\pard\qj\sl240\slmult1 \sb60 \fi0 In transparent languages, we do not expect restrictions on what semantic units can be chosen as predicates.\par
\pard\qj\sl240\slmult1 \fi300 In Sri Lanka Malay, verbs, adjectives, modals and locatives can be used as predicates without further measures being taken. Only verbs can take TAM-prefixes though. TAM for other predicates must be expressed lexically.{\up16\chftn}
{\*\footnote \pard\plain\s246\f13\fs20 {\up16\chftn}Adjectives can convert to verbs and afford all of verbal morphology, but they are no longer adjectives then.}
