}\pard\qj\sl240\slmult1 \sb120 \fi0 {\s4\ql\sb240\sa60\keepn\f13\b\fs32 {\*\bkmkstart BMex_consecutio}4.3{\*\bkmkend BMex_consecutio}  No tense copying\par
}\pard\qj\sl240\slmult1 \sb60 \fi0 Transparent languages are expected to show always the \lquote real\rquote  tense value from the representational level in morphosyntax. Changing tenses (tense copying, consecutio temporum) are not expected. Thus, constructions like English \i He said that he had two brothers \i0 , where the past tense is used despite the present tense meaning are not expected to occur in transparent languages. Inded, SLM does not show tense copying.\par
